<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 26 at 9:14AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A band of heavy snow will continue to affect portions of
North- Central Montana this morning...
A band of heavy snow extends from near Havre to near Stanford as
of 9:15 this morning, and is slowly moving eastward. Snowfall
rates exceeding 1 inch per hour are occurring with this band of
snow. Consider delaying travel as this band moves through, but if
you must travel, give yourself extra time to arrive safely to your
destination. You should also carry a winter safety kit, as
temperatures across the area are near or below zero, with wind
chill values lower than 20 below zero in spots.</description>
